column3: Somehow I cannot get travis to pass here. Even though "travis: for travis generating an extra build" is on the 0.10 branch, it still creates an extra empty test target.\n@theuni any idea?\n
@laanwj Travis has been doing this in a lot of places randomly. That extra target is bogus and can be ignored.\n

@btcdrak Sure, but we managed to correct that on the branch by twiddling with the `.travis.yml` file (which is why it doesn't appear in master pullreqs or the 0.11 one). But somehow it does here. And it's not random, I re-triggered it three times.\n

Might be resolved by rebasing on top of the updated 0.10.

The last build [81320710](https://travis-ci.org/bitcoin/bitcoin/builds/81320710) also refers to a non-existing commit https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/0dc55a8e8992c610c84adfd364d5c88a187d779a.
Rebased as suggested; tests passing now.\n

Ah nice.

Looks good to me. I can confirm that the code for 0.10 is the same as for master and 0.11.

The softfork status via `"getblockchaininfo"` is missing in this branch (i.e. 08dbe20f7f8d8dbefb7955d4470b891ac2344ba5 + f59bc924a2af3e4dc0512eeeb5610885781f24fd) though.
@dexX7 That code depends on the consensusParams stuff, which was added in v0.11.0, so I didn't bother rebasing it for v0.10.x - I expect on a small handful of miners to be using v0.10.x anyway.\n
Tested. Looks good to me. ACK \n
